# CHAPTER II

REFUTATION OF INCOMPLETE AND SUPERFICIAL (DOCTRINE)

\[1\]

THERE are in the Buddhist doctrines, to state briefly, the five grades
(of development), beginning with the most superficial, and ending with
the most profound teachings. (They are as follows:) (1) The Doctrine for
Men and Devas; (2) the Doctrine of the Hinayanists; (3) the Mahayana
Doctrine of Dharma-laksana; (4) the Mahayana Doctrine of the Nihilists
\[2\]; (5) the Ekaydna Doctrine that teaches the Ultimate Reality.\[3\]

