the spiritual needs of the uninitiated, preached a doctrine concerning
good or bad Karma as the cause, and its retribution as the effect, in
the three existences (of the past, the present, and the future). That
is, one who commits the tenfold sin\[4\] must be reborn after death in
hell, when these sins are of the highest grade;\[5\] among Pretas,\[6\]
when of the middle grade; and among

